    {
        "desc": "You find yourself in an abandoned hole. Dust covers everything, and yet the\nfurniture appears surprisingly whole. However, closer examination reveals\ncenturies of rot. Judging by its size, and the rusty and useless remains of\npickaxes and other mining tools, this must once have been the home of a group of\ndwarves. You find the torn remainders of a journal, yet little of it is now\nintact. It would seem that though this was once a natural cave, it was later\nenlarged as a living area; the room extends further north, sloping downward\nslightly, and ending in a rough door of wooden planks, which cover a wide\nopening. The walls seem to be sturdy and well built, save for the east wall,\nwhich has either collapsed over the course of time, or was perhaps constructed\nwith some haste, and little skill.\n",
